goals.question: Which genus has the highest usage of Neomycin?

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['Bacteria'] == b]['Penicillin'] for b in data['Bacteria'].unique()])
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['Bacteria'].unique(), rotation=90)
    ax.set_ylabel('Penicillin')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin across different bacteria?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['Streptomycin'], data['Neomycin'])
    plt.xlabel('Streptomycin')
    plt.ylabel('Neomycin')
    plt.title('How does the usage of Streptomycin compare to Neomycin?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by=['Gram_Staining'])
    data = data.groupby(['Bacteria', 'Gram_Staining']).size().reset_index(name='counts')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax.bar(data['Bacteria'], data['counts'], color=data['Gram_Staining'].map({'positive': 'blue', 'negative': 'red'}))
    ax.set_xlabel('Bacteria')
    ax.set_ylabel('Counts')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of Gram Staining across different bacteria?')
    ax.legend(['Gram Positive', 'Gram Negative'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist([data[data['Gram_Staining'] == 'positive']['Penicillin'], data[data['Gram_Staining'] == 'negative']['Penicillin']], bins=20, color=['green', 'red'], label=['Gram Positive', 'Gram Negative'])
    plt.axvline(x=data['Penicillin'].mean(), color='black', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean Penicillin Usage')
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('Penicillin Usage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin usage by Gram Staining?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='Neomycin', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['Genus'], data['Neomycin'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c', '#d62728'])
    plt.axhline(y=data['Neomycin'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label=f"Max Neomycin usage: {data['Neomycin'].max():.2f}")
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.xlabel('Genus')
    plt.ylabel('Neomycin')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
